  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "what_changes_gui",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2.4 What Changes Outside the GUI\n",
    "\n",
    "Opening a dynamic simulation headlessly is not the same as pressing *Run* in the GUI.\n",
    "Several operations that the GUI handles in the background need to be reproduced explicitly\n",
    "when driving the simulation from Python.\n",
    "\n",
    "**The schedule does not run automatically.**  \n",
    "The event definitions are available through the DynamicsManager, but the GUI scheduler loop\n",
    "is not active in headless execution. In this notebook, the two pressure setpoint changes are\n",
    "reproduced manually in Python at the correct simulation times.\n",
    "\n",
    "**PID controllers need to be triggered explicitly.**  \n",
    "After each dynamic solver step, the script calls the internal DWSIM PID calculations.\n",
    "Python is not replacing the PID algorithm — it is controlling when the existing controllers\n",
    "are evaluated.\n",
    "\n",
    "**The historian is not available after reloading.**  \n",
    "Monitored variable data from the GUI historian is held in memory during a GUI session and\n",
    "is not written back to the `.dwxmz` file. If the script needs a record of the run, it has\n",
    "to collect the variables during the simulation loop — which is exactly what this notebook does.\n",
    "\n",
    "These are not limitations so much as a different operating model: the script takes explicit\n",
    "responsibility for everything the GUI was handling implicitly. That explicitness is what makes\n",
    "the execution reproducible and extensible."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9f7b9c49",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Dynamic Simulation Run\n",
    "\n",
    "We reload the flowsheet to guarantee a clean initial state, then run the dynamic loop —\n",
    "step by step — applying the scheduled setpoint changes at the correct simulation times.\n",
    "\n",
    "Python acts as the execution layer: it controls when events are applied, when the dynamic\n",
    "solver advances, when the controllers act, and when process variables are recorded.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Loop pattern:**\n",
    "```\n",
    "for each time step:\n",
    "    apply pressure setpoint event, if required\n",
    "    update integrator timestamp\n",
    "    advance the DWSIM dynamic solver        <- DWSIMSolver.SolveFlowsheet(fs, 1)\n",
    "    call the internal DWSIM PID calculations\n",
    "    record pressure, level, setpoint\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Why `DWSIMSolver.SolveFlowsheet(fs, 1)` and not `RequestCalculationAndWait`?**  \n",
    "> `RequestCalculationAndWait` always invokes the steady-state solver regardless of `DynamicMode`.\n",
    "> The correct headless dynamic solver call is `DWSIMSolver.SolveFlowsheet(fs, 1)`.\n",
    "> A script can appear to execute correctly while silently running steady-state steps instead\n",
    "> of dynamic ones if the wrong solver call is used."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "09179bde",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initial state — P: 3.025 bar  Level: 0.307 m  SP: 2.0 bar\n",
      "Running 360 steps (1800 s / 30 min) ...\n",
      "  t =   180 s ( 3 min): PID-012 SP → 5.0 bar\n",
      "  t =   600 s (10 min): PID-012 SP → 2.0 bar\n",
      "\n",
      "Done.\n",
      "Final state  — P: 1.926 bar  Level: 0.301 m\n",
      "Wall time    : 50.5 s\n",
      "Sim time     : 1800 s\n",
      "Speedup      : 36x real time\n",
      "Per step     : 140.2 ms/step\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import time\n",
    "from System import DateTime, TimeSpan\n",
    "from DWSIM.FlowsheetSolver import FlowsheetSolver as DWSIMSolver\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Fresh load — guarantees reproducible initial state ─────────────────────────\n",
    "fs = auto.LoadFlowsheet(SIM_PATH)\n",
    "fs.DynamicMode = True\n",
    "\n",
    "objects = {\n",
    "    obj.GraphicObject.Tag: obj.__implementation__\n",
    "    for obj in fs.SimulationObjects.Values\n",
    "    if obj.GraphicObject is not None\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "pid12 = objects[\"PID-012\"]\n",
    "pid13 = objects[\"PID-013\"]\n",
    "sg    = objects[\"SG-01\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── DynamicsManager — reset integrator to t = 0 ───────────────────────────────\n",
    "dm        = fs.DynamicsManager.__implementation__\n",
    "integ_key = list(dm.IntegratorList.Keys)[0]\n",
    "integ     = dm.IntegratorList[integ_key].__implementation__\n",
    "dm.CurrentSchedule = list(dm.ScheduleList.Keys)[0]\n",
    "integ.CurrentTime  = DateTime(1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Simulation parameters ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "dt      = 5           # integration step [s] — matches integrator config\n",
    "t_end   = 30 * 60     # total simulation time [s]\n",
    "n_steps = t_end // dt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scheduled setpoint changes for PID-012 (pressure controller)\n",
    "# key = simulation time [s], value = new setpoint [bar]\n",
    "sp_events = {\n",
    "    3  * 60: 5.0,   # t = 3 min  → SP = 5 bar\n",
    "    10 * 60: 2.0,   # t = 10 min → SP = 2 bar\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── History arrays ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "t_hist    = np.zeros(n_steps + 1)\n",
    "p_hist    = np.zeros(n_steps + 1)\n",
    "lv_hist   = np.zeros(n_steps + 1)\n",
    "sp_hist   = np.zeros(n_steps + 1)\n",
    "mv12_hist = np.zeros(n_steps + 1)\n",
    "mv13_hist = np.zeros(n_steps + 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Record initial state (t = 0)\n",
    "t_hist[0]    = 0\n",
    "p_hist[0]    = sg.GetDynamicProperty(\"Operating Pressure\") / 1e5  # Pa → bar\n",
    "lv_hist[0]   = sg.GetDynamicProperty(\"Liquid Level\")               # m\n",
    "sp_hist[0]   = pid12.SetPoint\n",
    "mv12_hist[0] = pid12.MVValue\n",
    "mv13_hist[0] = pid13.MVValue\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Initial state — P: {p_hist[0]:.3f} bar  Level: {lv_hist[0]:.3f} m  SP: {sp_hist[0]:.1f} bar\")\n",
    "print(f\"Running {n_steps} steps ({t_end} s / {t_end//60} min) ...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Dynamic loop ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "t_wall_start = time.perf_counter()\n",
    "\n",
    "for step in range(1, n_steps + 1):\n",
    "    t_s = step * dt\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Apply scheduled setpoint changes\n",
    "    if t_s in sp_events:\n",
    "        pid12.SetPoint = sp_events[t_s]\n",
    "        print(f\"  t = {t_s:>5} s ({t_s // 60:>2} min): PID-012 SP → {sp_events[t_s]} bar\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Advance integrator clock\n",
    "    integ.CurrentTime = DateTime(1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0) + TimeSpan.FromSeconds(t_s)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Dynamic solver step\n",
    "    DWSIMSolver.SolveFlowsheet(fs, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Update PID controllers\n",
    "    pid12.Calculate()\n",
    "    pid13.Calculate()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Record process variables\n",
    "    t_hist[step]    = t_s\n",
    "    p_hist[step]    = sg.GetDynamicProperty(\"Operating Pressure\") / 1e5\n",
    "    lv_hist[step]   = sg.GetDynamicProperty(\"Liquid Level\")\n",
    "    sp_hist[step]   = pid12.SetPoint\n",
    "    mv12_hist[step] = pid12.MVValue\n",
    "    mv13_hist[step] = pid13.MVValue\n",
    "\n",
    "t_wall = time.perf_counter() - t_wall_start\n",
    "speedup = t_end / t_wall\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDone.\")\n",
    "print(f\"Final state  — P: {p_hist[-1]:.3f} bar  Level: {lv_hist[-1]:.3f} m\")\n",
    "print(f\"Wall time    : {t_wall:.1f} s\")\n",
    "print(f\"Sim time     : {t_end} s\")\n",
    "print(f\"Speedup      : {speedup:.0f}x real time\")\n",
    "print(f\"Per step     : {t_wall / n_steps * 1000:.1f} ms/step\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4900dad5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
