  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "80ecad27",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5.2 Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pressure (PID-012):**  \n",
    "The simulation starts with separator pressure around 3 bar, above the initial pressure setpoint\n",
    "of 2 bar. The pressure controller is already driving the pressure down when the run begins.\n",
    "\n",
    "At **t = 3 min**, the setpoint steps from 2 to 5 bar. The controller closes the gas outlet valve,\n",
    "allowing pressure to build toward the new target. The separator reaches approximately 4.8 bar.\n",
    "\n",
    "At **t = 10 min**, the setpoint returns to 2 bar. The gas outlet valve opens aggressively,\n",
    "producing a pressure undershoot to around 1.4 bar before the loop recovers.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Level (PID-013):**  \n",
    "The level controller maintains SP = 0.3 m throughout the scenario. Pressure changes create\n",
    "hydraulic coupling: the level moves during the pressure transients, but PID-013 rejects the\n",
    "disturbance and brings the separator back to its target.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Execution performance:**  \n",
    "The 30-minute scenario runs in approximately 50 seconds of wall time — **~36x faster than\n",
    "real time**. That speedup makes automated scenario generation practical: instead of running\n",
    "one dynamic case interactively, the same execution pattern can be reused across many variants\n",
    "with different setpoints, disturbance timings, or initial conditions.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5.3 Key API Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "The table below summarises the non-obvious API discoveries made during this case study,\n",
    "relevant to anyone automating DWSIM dynamic simulations from Python.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Topic | Correct pattern | Common mistake |\n",
    "|-------|----------------|----------------|\n",
    "| Dynamic solver | `DWSIMSolver.SolveFlowsheet(fs, 1)` | `RequestCalculationAndWait` (runs SS solver) |\n",
    "| Schedule execution | Reproduce events manually in Python | `dm.RunSchedule()` (GUI-only, raises error headless) |\n",
    "| Event trigger time | `ev.TimeStamp` | `ev.TriggerTime` (does not exist) |\n",
    "| Event object reference | `ev.SimulationObjectID` is a GUID needs lookup | Using as tag directly |\n",
    "| PID setpoint | `pid.SetPoint` | `pid.SetPointAbs` (does not exist) |\n",
    "| PID CV/MV wiring | Resolved automatically via `ControlledObjectData` in this sample | Always requires explicit `ControlledObject` assignment |\n",
    "| Valve opening property | `PROP_VA_5` | - |\n",
    "| Monitored variable history | Not persisted in `.dwxmz` file | Attempting to read after reload returns empty dict |"
   ]
  },
